m_q.target_metric: Years where Fraud reports count is at least 50% of total reports (Fraud + Identity Theft + Other)
sub_questions: Calculate Fraud percentage of total reports per year

scale_issues: All count columns appear to be integers, no scaling issues evident

format_notes: First column is Year, followed by three report type columns
Data appears clean with no missing values in sample

constraints: Year values should be sequential from 2001-2024 based on shape [24,4]
All count columns should be non-negative integers
Total reports = Fraud + Identity Theft + Other should be positive
statistical_tests: Verify that sum of three report types equals total reports for each year
output_format_requirements: List of years where condition is met
Could optionally include Fraud percentage for each year
